Apprehensions for 2019

excel_file <- "~/git/zbiory/cudzoziemcy/Straz graniczna/niel pobyt 2018-2019-szczegoly.xlsx"
excel_sheets(excel_file) %>%
  set_names() %>%
  map_df(~ read_excel(path = excel_file, sheet = .x, skip = 5, 
                      col_names = c("appreh", "place", "woj", "citizen_iso", "citizen_name", 
                                                  "women_0_17", "women_18_59", "women_60",
                                                  "men_0_17", "men_18_64", "men_65", "total"),
                      col_types = c(rep("text", 5), rep("numeric", 7))) %>%
           fill(appreh, place, woj) %>%
           filter(str_detect(appreh, "Suma|RAZEM|zatrzymanie", negate = T)) %>%
           group_by(appreh, place, citizen_iso, citizen_name) %>%
           summarise_at(vars(women_0_17:men_65), sum, na.rm = T), .id = "half") %>%
  mutate(year = str_extract(half, "\\d{4}"),
         half = str_extract(half, "I{1,2}")) %>%
  filter(year == 2019) -> sg

sg %>%
  ungroup() %>%
  count(year, half, appreh, place, wt = women_18_59+women_60+men_18_64+men_65) %>%
  spread(place, n, fill = 0) %>%
  mutate(appreh = ifelse(appreh == "tak", "yes", "no")) %>%
  select(year, half, `same year` = appreh, `within country`= kraj, `airports` = `lotnicza zewnętrzna`,
         `Ukraine` = `Ukraina`, `Russia` = Rosja, `Belarus` = `Białoruś`) %>%
  xtable(caption = "sfsfsa", label = "tab-sg-basic", digits = 0) %>%
  print.xtable(include.rownames = F, caption = "afasf", caption.placement = "top", format.args = list(big.mark = ","))

Police data for 2019

map_df(1:4, ~ read_excel(path = "~/git/zbiory/cudzoziemcy/Policja/Osoba-cudzoziemcy-rok 2019.xls",  
                         sheet = .x, 
                         skip = 2, .name_repair = janitor::make_clean_names) %>%
  fill(id_ksip_oio, wiek, plec, obywatelstwo, data_wprowadzenia_rok, data_wprowadzenia_kwartal),
  #mutate(pesel_tak_nie = ifelse(is.na(pesel_tak_nie), "NIE", pesel_tak_nie)),
  .id = 'sheet') %>%
  mutate(sheet = case_when(sheet == 1 ~ "process",
                           sheet == 2 ~ "criminal",
                           sheet == 3 ~ "searching",
                           sheet == 4  ~ "traffic")) %>%
  group_by(sheet, id_ksip_oio) %>%
  fill(pesel_tak_nie)  %>%
  ungroup() -> police

police %>%
  mutate(half = ifelse(data_wprowadzenia_kwartal %in% 1:2, "I", "II")) %>%
  distinct(sheet, id_ksip_oio, pesel_tak_nie, half) %>%
  mutate(pesel_tak_nie = replace_na(pesel_tak_nie, "NIE"), 
         PESEL= factor(pesel_tak_nie, c("TAK", "NIE"), c("Yes", "No"), ordered = T)) %>%
  count(year = as.character(2019), half, PESEL, type = sheet) %>%
  spread(type, n, fill = 0) %>%
  select(year:PESEL, process, searching, traffic, criminal) %>%
  xtable(caption = "sfsfsa", label = "tab-sg-basic", digits = 0) %>%
  print.xtable(include.rownames = F, caption = "afasf", caption.placement = "top", format.args = list(big.mark = ","))

PESEL data for 2019

1 = brak adresu w Polsce 2 = aktualny pobyt czasowy 3 = aktualny pobyt stały 4 = wymeldowny donikąd 5 = nieaktualny pobyt czasowy 6 = kraj zamieszkania poza Polską) Płeć: 1-kob, 2-mężczy Wiek - podział na ekonomiczne grupy wieku: 1 = - wiek przedprodukcyjny — do 17 lat - wiek produkcyjny: 2 = - dla męczyzn — 18-64, 3 = - dla kobiet — 18-59, - wiek poprodukcyjny 4 =- dla mężczyzn — 65 i więcej, 5 = - dla kobiet — 60 i więcej.

Stan cywilny 1 = kawaler, panna; 2 = żonaty, zamężna; 3 = wdowiec, wdowa; 4 = rozwiedziony, rozwiedziona; null = brak danych

Woj Miejsce zameldowania lub ostatniego zameldowania (jeżeli jest podane w rejestrze PESEL). Kody w nawiasach null = brak danych DOLNOŚLĄSKIE (02) KUJAWSKO-POMORSKIE (04) LUBELSKIE (06) LUBUSKIE (08) ŁÓDZKIE (10) MAŁOPOLSKIE (12) MAZOWIECKIE (14) OPOLSKIE (16) PODKARPACKIE (18) PODLASKIE (20) POMORSKIE (22) ŚLĄSKIE (24) ŚWIĘTOKRZYSKIE (26) WARMIŃSKO-MAZURSKIE (28) WIELKOPOLSKIE (30) ZACHODNIOPOMORSKIE (32)

pesel_prepared %>%
  filter(half %in% c("I", "II")) %>%
  full_join(sg_prepared %>% rename(country_name_sg = country_name)) %>%
  full_join(police_prepared %>% rename(country_name_police = country_name)) %>% 
  select(half, age, sex, country_iso3n, 
         country_name_pesel = country_name, country_name_sg, country_name_police, pesel, border, matches("police")) %>%
  mutate(eu = countrycode(country_iso3n, "genc3n", "eu28"),
         country = countrycode(country_iso3n, "genc3n", "un.name.en"),
         country = case_when(country_iso3n == "999" ~ "other",
                             country_iso3n == "998" ~ "other",
                             country_iso3n == "567" ~ "Kosovo",
                             country_iso3n == "275" ~ "Palestine",
                             country_iso3n == "158" ~ "Taiwan",
                             country_iso3n == "336" ~ "Vatican city",
                             country_iso3n == "016" ~ "American Samoa",
                             TRUE ~ country)) %>%
  mutate_at(vars(pesel:police_all), replace_na, 0)  %>%
  filter(is.na(eu)) %>%
  arrange(country, country_iso3n, half, age, sex, pesel, border, police_nonreg, police_reg, police_all) %>%
  select(country, country_iso3n, half, age, sex, pesel, border, police_nonreg, police_reg, police_all) -> countries_all

countries_all %>%
  group_by(country, country_iso3n, half, age, sex = factor(sex)) %>%
  summarise_at(vars(pesel:police_all), sum) %>%
  mutate(country = ifelse(border > 0 & police_all > 0 & police_all / pesel < 1, country, "other")) %>%
  group_by(country, half, age, sex) %>%
  summarise_at(vars(pesel:police_all), sum) -> m
